value.0: Before you stands a mage who eyes you with suspicion, as if expecting anyone to be an assassin or some such other.
These robes are infused with a darkly, vile magic, and they're splatted with much blood. You absently wonder about their creation.

Many moons ago, the City of Tarkuul existed in a much sinister glory, whence some crusading paladins raized it and naught but the gate bars remained.

You now hold one of these bars, unrusted by time, since Tarkuul's sinister magic has steeped into it's shaft.
This woman seems to be poring through numerous books relating to the elemental planes.

Value.value: You've the look of a strapping adventurer, wot wot!
I am doing research into the strange effects the local insect population has been exhibiting.
They seem to be suffused with elemental fire energy, an oddity for a simple giant ant.
Very interesting. So it seems the magma flows beneath their colony, granting them elemental infusion.. I must ponder this!
Have you made note of all eight ant hills? Finding the queen's lair will likely provide even greater answers.
My thanks for your help with this important bit of research!
Could you make your way to the eastern coast of the isle and make note of all eight ant hills?
If you can get to the deepest part of their colony, that will likely provide the greatest insight!
